>> Sreenivasan: GOOD EVENING.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.057
THANKS FOR JOINING US.

00:57.057 --> 00:58.091
IT'S MONDAY MORNING IN ASIA AND

00:58.091 --> 00:59.192
THE SEARCH FOR A MISSING AIRASIA

00:59.192 --> 01:00.527
JETLINER CARRYING 162 PEOPLE IS

01:00.527 --> 01:01.995
RESUMING.

01:01.995 --> 01:03.864
THE AIRBUS DISAPPEARED FROM

01:03.864 --> 01:05.532
RADAR SCREENS ABOUT 40 MINUTES

01:05.532 --> 01:09.002
AFTER TAKING OFF FROM INDONESIA

01:09.002 --> 01:09.903
ON ROUTE TO SINGAPORE.

01:09.903 --> 01:11.071
THE NEWSHOUR'S ZACHARY GREEN HAS

01:11.071 --> 01:13.106
MORE ON THE INVESTIGATION.

01:13.106 --> 01:14.441
>> Reporter: AT SINGAPORE'S

01:14.441 --> 01:15.909
CHANGI AIRPORT, FRIENDS AND

01:15.909 --> 01:17.577
RELATIVES GATHERED TO AWAIT NEWS

01:17.577 --> 01:19.046
ABOUT AIRASIA FLIGHT 8501, WHICH

01:19.046 --> 01:23.283
DISAPPEARED EARLY THIS MORNING.

01:23.283 --> 01:24.718
AMONG THOSE WAITING, THE FIANCEE

01:24.718 --> 01:26.119
OF A YOUNG MAN WHO HAD BEEN

01:26.119 --> 01:32.626
TRAVELING WITH RELATIVES.

01:32.626 --> 01:33.560
>> (translated): IT WAS

01:33.560 --> 01:34.428
SUPPOSED TO BE THEIR LAST

01:34.428 --> 01:35.195
VACATION, BEFORE US--WE GOT

01:35.195 --> 01:36.096
MARRIED.

01:36.096 --> 01:36.897
IT WAS TO BE HIS LAST VACATION

01:36.897 --> 01:37.965
WITH HIS FAMILY.

01:37.965 --> 01:38.899
>> Reporter: THE FLIGHT TOOK OFF

01:38.899 --> 01:39.766
AT 5:35 A.M. LOCAL TIME FROM

01:39.766 --> 01:40.534
SURABAYA, INDONESIA'S SECOND-

01:40.534 --> 01:41.768
LARGEST CITY.

01:41.768 --> 01:42.636
THE SCHEDULED FLIGHT TIME TO

01:42.636 --> 01:43.603
SINGAPORE WAS ONE HOUR AND 55

01:43.603 --> 01:45.005
MINUTES.

01:45.005 --> 01:46.406
BUT AT 6:13 AM, 38 MINUTES AFTER

01:46.406 --> 01:47.975
TAKEOFF, THE PILOT RADIOED AIR

01:47.975 --> 01:49.276
TRAFFIC CONTROL, ASKING TO

01:49.276 --> 01:50.544
CHANGE COURSE AND INCREASE

01:50.544 --> 01:54.781
ALTITUDE TO AVOID STORM CLOUDS.

01:54.781 --> 01:55.782
THERE WERE REPORTS OF LIGHTNING

01:55.782 --> 01:57.484
IN THE AREA.

01:57.484 --> 01:59.052
THE FLIGHT WAS LAST SEEN ON

01:59.052 --> 02:00.854
RADAR THREE MINUTES LATER AT

02:00.854 --> 02:02.889
6:16 AM, NEAR BELITUNG ISLAND IN

02:02.889 --> 02:04.091
THE JAVA SEA.

02:04.091 --> 02:05.859
A MINUTE LATER, IT WAS GONE.

02:05.859 --> 02:07.094
ACCORDING TO AN INDONESIAN

02:07.094 --> 02:08.929
TRANSPORTATION OFFICIAL, NO

02:08.929 --> 02:10.564
DISTRESS SIGNAL HAD BEEN SENT

02:10.564 --> 02:12.199
OUT.

02:12.199 --> 02:13.633
SEARCH AND RESCUE TEAMS FROM

02:13.633 --> 02:14.968
INDONESIA, SINGAPORE, AND

02:14.968 --> 02:16.403
MALAYSIA SPENT SEVERAL HOURS

02:16.403 --> 02:18.872
SUNDAY SEARCHING FOR ANY SIGN OF

02:18.872 --> 02:21.308
THE PLANE, AN AIRBUS A320.

02:21.308 --> 02:22.409
BUT AS NIGHT FELL, OFFICIALS

02:22.409 --> 02:24.544
HALTED THE SEARCH UNTIL MORNING.

02:24.544 --> 02:26.580
THE UNITED STATES, THE UNITED

02:26.580 --> 02:28.281
KINGDOM, AUSTRALIA, SOUTH KOREA,

02:28.281 --> 02:29.549
AND INDIA HAVE ALL VOLUNTEERED

02:29.549 --> 02:33.620
SEARCH AND RESCUE TEAMS.

02:33.620 --> 02:34.921
>> (translated): I HEARD MANY

02:34.921 --> 02:36.023
RUMORS FROM PEOPLE AND I SAID

02:36.023 --> 02:37.024
THE RUMORS ARE NOT TRUE THAT THE

02:37.024 --> 02:38.492
PLANE HAS BEEN FOUND AND

02:38.492 --> 02:39.760
WRECKAGE HAS BEEN FOUND-- THIS

02:39.760 --> 02:41.194
IS NOT TRUE.

02:41.194 --> 02:42.529
>> Reporter: TONY FERNANDES,

02:42.529 --> 02:43.764
CHIEF EXECUTIVE OF AIRASIA, A

02:43.764 --> 02:45.032
BUDGET CARRIER BASED IN

02:45.032 --> 02:46.099
MALAYSIA, ALSO CAUTIONED AGAINST

02:46.099 --> 02:47.134
SPECULATION.

02:47.134 --> 02:48.502
>> WE DO NOT KNOW WHAT'S

02:48.502 --> 02:49.903
HAPPENED YET, SO WE'LL WAIT FOR

02:49.903 --> 02:51.104
THE ACCIDENT INVESTIGATION TO

02:51.104 --> 02:54.908
REALLY FIND OUT WHAT'S HAPPENED.

02:54.908 --> 02:57.144
OUR CONCERN RIGHT NOW IS FOR THE

02:57.144 --> 02:58.912
RELATIVES AND FOR THE NEXT OF

02:58.912 --> 03:00.614
KIN, THERE IS NOTHING MORE

03:00.614 --> 03:03.250
IMPORTANT TO US FOR OUR CREW'S

03:03.250 --> 03:04.518
FAMILY, AND FOR OUR PASSENGERS'

03:04.518 --> 03:06.219
FAMILIES, THAT WE LOOK AFTER

03:06.219 --> 03:07.054
THEM.

03:07.054 --> 03:08.088
>> Reporter: AIRASIA HAS HAD A

03:08.088 --> 03:09.189
CLEAN SAFETY RECORD SINCE THE

03:09.189 --> 03:10.457
COMPANY BEGAN OPERATING IN

03:10.457 --> 03:13.160
MALAYSIA 13 YEARS AGO.

03:13.160 --> 03:14.561
THE PLANE THAT WENT MISSING HAD

03:14.561 --> 03:19.032
UNDERGONE MAINTENANCE JUST A

03:19.032 --> 03:20.133
MONTH BEFORE.

03:20.133 --> 03:21.601
LAST MARCH, MALAYSIA AIRLINES

03:21.601 --> 03:25.072
FLIGHT 370 DISAPPEARED WITH 239

03:25.072 --> 03:26.373
PEOPLE ABOARD, ON ROUTE FROM

03:26.373 --> 03:27.607
KUALA LUMPUR TO BEIJING.

03:27.607 --> 03:28.642
IT'S NEVER BEEN FOUND.

03:28.642 --> 03:29.743
IN JULY, MALAYSIA AIRLINES

03:29.743 --> 03:30.844
FLIGHT 17 WAS SHOT DOWN OVER

03:30.844 --> 03:32.212
EASTERN UKRAINE, KILLING ALL 298

03:32.212 --> 03:39.186
PEOPLE ON BOARD.

03:39.186 --> 03:40.387
>> Sreenivasan: A FERRY CARRYING

03:40.387 --> 03:41.621
NEARLY 500 PASSENGERS AND CREW

