♪

06:27.120 --> 06:28.822
>> Reporter: TIMOTHY FUGATT, THE

06:28.822 --> 06:30.357
MINISTER OF MUSIC AT THIS CHURCH

06:30.357 --> 06:31.791
NEAR CHILDERSBURG, ALABAMA, SAYS

06:31.791 --> 06:33.693
THAT IT'S HIS DEEP FAITH IN GOD

06:33.693 --> 06:35.128
THAT GOT HIM THROUGH SOME TOUGH

06:35.128 --> 06:35.962
TIMES.

06:35.962 --> 06:36.997
HIS SON, COLE, WAS BORN WITH A

06:36.997 --> 06:38.431
RARE BRAIN DISEASE.

06:38.431 --> 06:39.599
>> THE SPHERES IN HIS BRAIN

06:39.599 --> 06:40.634
DIDN'T DIVIDE PROPERLY.

06:40.634 --> 06:47.007
SO PRETTY MUCH WHEN YOU LOOK

06:47.007 --> 06:47.874
THROUGH A C.T. SCAN, IT WAS

06:47.874 --> 06:49.542
NOTHING BUT FLUID.

06:49.542 --> 06:50.577
>> Reporter: BUT LIFE GOT EVEN

06:50.577 --> 06:51.745
TOUGHER AFTER A SEEMINGLY MINOR

06:51.745 --> 06:52.779
INCIDENT IN DECEMBER OF 2010

06:52.779 --> 06:53.713
WHEN HE WAS PULLED OVER BY

06:53.713 --> 06:54.714
POLICE AND TICKETED FOR AN

06:54.714 --> 06:55.915
EXPIRED LICENSE PLATE TAG.

06:55.915 --> 06:56.783
>> I WAS COMING FROM THE

06:56.783 --> 06:57.884
HOSPITAL WHERE HAD BEEN STAYING

06:57.884 --> 07:01.221
WITH COLE THERE IN THE HOSPITAL.

07:01.221 --> 07:02.222
AND AS I COME INTO TOWN, THEY

07:02.222 --> 07:04.224
HAD A TRAFFIC CHECKPOINT.

07:04.224 --> 07:05.825
TIMOTHY'S WIFE, KRISTY, HAD ALSO

07:05.825 --> 07:08.028
GOTTEN TICKETS FOR TWO TRAFFIC

07:08.028 --> 07:09.996
INFRACTIONS AND BOTH WERE

07:09.996 --> 07:11.231
ORDERED TO APPEAR IN THE

07:11.231 --> 07:12.365
CHILDERSBURG MUNICIPAL COURT.

07:12.365 --> 07:14.000
THE FUGATTS TOLD THE JUDGE ABOUT

07:14.000 --> 07:15.669
THEIR HOSPITALIZED SON AND WERE

07:15.669 --> 07:16.836
BOTH FOUND "NOT GUILTY", AS

07:16.836 --> 07:17.904
THESE COURT DOCUMENTS SHOW.

07:17.904 --> 07:21.675
BUT THE JUDGE RULED THAT THE TWO

07:21.675 --> 07:23.243
STILL HAD TO PAY COURT COSTS OF

07:23.243 --> 07:25.178
ABOUT $500.

07:25.178 --> 07:26.413
DURING THIS PERIOD, TIMOTHY

07:26.413 --> 07:27.847
FUGATT SAYS HE WAS SPENDING SO

07:27.847 --> 07:29.182
MUCH TIME AT THE HOSPITAL WITH

07:29.182 --> 07:30.317
HIS SON THAT HE COULDN'T HOLD

07:30.317 --> 07:31.318
DOWN A JOB, AND WITH HIS WIFE

07:31.318 --> 07:33.086
ALSO NOT WORKING, THEY COULDN'T

07:33.086 --> 07:34.554
AFFORD TO PAY THE COURT COSTS.

07:34.554 --> 07:35.955
SO THEIR CASE WAS TURNED OVER TO

07:35.955 --> 07:37.424
JUDICIAL CORRECTIONS SERVICES, A

07:37.424 --> 07:39.292
PRIVATE COMPANY THAT COLLECTS

07:39.292 --> 07:42.762
FINES FOR THE CITY.

07:42.762 --> 07:43.430
FUGATT SAYS THAT JUDICIAL

07:43.430 --> 07:45.932
CORRECTIONS SERVICES, KNOWN AS

07:45.932 --> 07:47.634
J.C.S., TOLD HIM THAT HE AND HIS

07:47.634 --> 07:49.302
WIFE COULD BE JAILED IF THEY

07:49.302 --> 07:51.871
DIDN'T PAY WHAT THEY OWED.

07:51.871 --> 07:53.306
>> THEY WOULD JUST PLAIN OUT

07:53.306 --> 07:54.407
SAY, YOU KNOW, "IF YOU CAN'T PAY

07:54.407 --> 07:55.642
THEN THEY'LL ISSUE YOU A WARRANT

07:55.642 --> 07:58.878
FOR YOUR ARREST."

07:58.878 --> 08:00.980
>> Reporter: DID THAT SCARE YOU?

08:00.980 --> 08:02.615
>> OF COURSE.

08:02.615 --> 08:03.883
>> Reporter: FUGATT SAYS HE DID

08:03.883 --> 08:04.918
THE BEST HE COULD TO PAY OFF HIS

08:04.918 --> 08:06.019
FAMILY'S FINES, BUT SAYS WHEN HE

08:06.019 --> 08:07.187
COULDN'T CONTINUE TO PAY AND HE

08:07.187 --> 08:08.788
AND HIS WIFE MISSED AT LEAST ONE

08:08.788 --> 08:09.889
COURT DATE, THEY WERE ARRESTED

08:09.889 --> 08:11.791
AND JAILED.

08:11.791 --> 08:13.159
>> I FELT COMPLETELY LIKE A

08:13.159 --> 08:14.394
CRIMINAL.

08:14.394 --> 08:15.829
I MEAN I DIDN'T SELL DRUGS.

08:15.829 --> 08:16.696
I DIDN'T BREAK INTO ANYONE'S

08:16.696 --> 08:18.031
HOME.

08:18.031 --> 08:19.666
I DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY.

08:19.666 --> 08:22.068
I HAD AN EXPIRED TAG.

08:22.068 --> 08:23.169
>> Reporter: SO YOU AND YOUR

08:23.169 --> 08:24.304
WIFE WERE FOUND NOT GUILTY OF

08:24.304 --> 08:25.238
THE TRAFFIC VIOLATIONS, BUT

08:25.238 --> 08:27.407
STILL YOU WERE BEING ARRESTED.

08:27.407 --> 08:30.877
>> WE WERE BEING ARRESTED, YES.

08:30.877 --> 08:33.880
I WAS VERY UPSET, VERY ANGRY.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.315
>> Reporter: THEY WERE RELEASED

08:35.315 --> 08:36.416
SEVERAL HOURS LATER WHEN A

08:36.416 --> 08:37.250
RELATIVE PAID A PORTION OF WHAT

08:37.250 --> 08:40.086
THEY OWED.

08:40.086 --> 08:41.388
THAT INCIDENT CONTRIBUTED TO THE

08:41.388 --> 08:42.622
FUGATTS' DECISION TO BECOME PART

08:42.622 --> 08:44.257
OF A LAWSUIT AGAINST JUDICIAL

08:44.257 --> 08:46.259
CORRECTIONS SERVICES AND THE

08:46.259 --> 08:48.395
TOWN OF CHILDERSBURG.

08:48.395 --> 08:49.462
THE SUIT ALLEGES THAT

08:49.462 --> 08:52.031
INCARCERATING PEOPLE WHO CAN'T

08:52.031 --> 08:53.400
PAY THEIR FINES VIOLATES THE

08:53.400 --> 08:53.900
CONSTITUTION.

08:53.900 --> 08:54.801
THOUGH SOME EXPERTS ARGUE THAT

08:54.801 --> 08:55.702
JAIL TIME IS LEGAL FOR THOSE WHO

08:55.702 --> 08:56.603
DON'T MAKE A GOOD FAITH EFFORT

08:56.603 --> 08:57.704
TO PAY THEIR FINES, IN 1971 THE

08:57.704 --> 08:58.805
SUPREME COURT RULED THAT THE

08:58.805 --> 08:59.739
CONSTITUTION PROHIBITS IMPOSING

08:59.739 --> 09:00.774
"A JAIL TERM SOLELY BECAUSE THE

09:00.774 --> 09:01.775
DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND CANNOT

09:01.775 --> 09:02.742
FORTHWITH PAY THE FINE IN FULL."

09:02.742 --> 09:03.710
>> THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT'S

09:03.710 --> 09:04.677
HAPPENING HERE.

09:04.677 --> 09:05.512
>> Reporter: DAVID DINELLI IS

09:05.512 --> 09:06.513
THE DEPUTY LEGAL DIRECTORY OF

09:06.513 --> 09:07.714
THE SOUTHERN POVERTY LAW CENTER,

09:07.714 --> 09:08.548
A NON-PROFIT CIVIL RIGHTS

09:08.548 --> 09:09.416
ORGANIZATION THAT IS NOT

09:09.416 --> 09:10.316
INVOLVED IN THE FUGATTS' LAWSUIT

09:10.316 --> 09:11.251
BUT HAS REPRESENTED OTHERS IN

09:11.251 --> 09:12.352
SIMILAR SITUATIONS.

09:12.352 --> 09:13.353
DINELLI ESTIMATES A 1,000 PEOPLE

09:13.353 --> 09:14.587
EVERY MONTH ARE GOING TO JAIL IN

09:14.587 --> 09:15.488
ALABAMA BECAUSE THEY CANNOT

09:15.488 --> 09:18.057
AFFORD TO PAY A FINE.

09:18.057 --> 09:18.992
>> EVERYONE THINKS THAT DEBTOR'S

09:18.992 --> 09:19.759
PRISON IS OVER.

09:19.759 --> 09:20.527
IT'S BEHIND US.

09:20.527 --> 09:21.194
IT ISN'T.

09:21.194 --> 09:22.395
AS A MATTER OF PRACTICE, AND IN

09:22.395 --> 09:23.763
SOME CASES, POLICY, THE COURTS

09:23.763 --> 09:26.065
ASK ONE QUESTION, "CAN YOU PAY

09:26.065 --> 09:27.434
THE FINE?"

09:27.434 --> 09:31.838
IF YOU CAN'T THEN YOU HAVE TO

09:31.838 --> 09:32.605
WHAT'S CALLED, "SIT IT OUT IN

09:32.605 --> 09:33.773
JAIL."

09:33.773 --> 09:34.808
THAT IS UNCONSTITUTIONAL UNLESS

09:34.808 --> 09:35.875
THE COURT FIRST CONDUCTS AN

09:35.875 --> 09:36.776
INQUIRY INTO WHETHER THEY'RE

09:36.776 --> 09:38.011
INDIGENT AND THE CAUSES FOR

09:38.011 --> 09:39.479
THEIR INABILITY TO PAY THE FINE.

09:39.479 --> 09:40.480
ROUTINELY WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE

09:40.480 --> 09:41.448
IS THAT NO SUCH INQUIRY IS

09:41.448 --> 09:43.016
UNDERTAKEN.

09:43.016 --> 09:44.717
>> DID ANYONE IN THE COURT EVERY

09:44.717 --> 09:45.418
TRY AND ASSESS WHETHER OR NOT

09:45.418 --> 09:47.020
YOU COULD AFFORD THE PAY THE

09:47.020 --> 09:51.724
FEES?

09:51.724 --> 09:53.326
>> NO, SIR.

09:53.326 --> 09:53.993
IT WAS JUST PASS AND GO.

09:53.993 --> 09:54.994
IT WAS REALLY FAST.

09:54.994 --> 09:57.063
IT WAS REALLY FAST.

09:57.063 --> 09:57.997
>> Reporter: COLLECTING FINES IS

09:57.997 --> 09:58.965
MORE IMPORTANT THAN EVER BECAUSE

09:58.965 --> 09:59.833
MANY CITIES FACE BUDGET

09:59.833 --> 10:00.533
SHORTFALLS.

10:00.533 --> 10:01.534
BUT THESE SAME CITIES DON'T HAVE

10:01.534 --> 10:02.335
THE PERSONNEL TO COLLECT THE

10:02.335 --> 10:03.169
FINES.

10:03.169 --> 10:04.370
SO INCREASINGLY THEY TURN TO

10:04.370 --> 10:05.972
WHAT ARE KNOWN AS PRIVATE

10:05.972 --> 10:07.407
PROBATION COMPANIES.

10:07.407 --> 10:08.608
THAT'S WHERE JUDICIAL

10:08.608 --> 10:11.744
CORRECTIONS SERVICES COMES IN.

10:11.744 --> 10:12.645
>> WE WERE APPROACHED BY THE

10:12.645 --> 10:13.680
PROBATION SERVICE.

10:13.680 --> 10:15.215
THEY FOUND A NICHE.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.349
>> Reporter: CHILDERSBURG

10:16.349 --> 10:17.383
OFFICIALS DECLINED TO SPEAK WITH

10:17.383 --> 10:18.618
US, SO WE MET WITH STEVEN BOONE,

10:18.618 --> 10:19.719
THE FINANCE DIRECTOR FOR

10:19.719 --> 10:21.054
MOUNTAIN BROOK, A CITY

10:21.054 --> 10:22.188
NEIGHBORING CHILDERSBURG THAT

10:22.188 --> 10:23.356
ALSO HIRED JUDICIAL CORRECTION

10:23.356 --> 10:24.991
SERVICES.

10:24.991 --> 10:26.159
ITS COURT IS ONE OF OVER A

10:26.159 --> 10:27.360
1,000, IN AT LEAST 12 STATES

10:27.360 --> 10:28.528
ACROSS THE COUNTRY, THAT'S HIRED

10:28.528 --> 10:29.329
A PRIVATE PROBATION COMPANY,

10:29.329 --> 10:31.531
ACCORDING TO HUMAN RIGHTS WATCH.

10:31.531 --> 10:32.932
JUDICIAL CORRECTION SERVICES

10:32.932 --> 10:35.301
COLLECTS FINES AT NO COST TO THE

10:35.301 --> 10:37.036
CITIES IT WORKS FOR.

10:37.036 --> 10:38.538
>> THEY'RE HELPING US TO BECOME

10:38.538 --> 10:39.639
MORE EFFICIENT, AND THEY'RE

10:39.639 --> 10:40.707
HELPING US TO ENSURE THAT WE

10:40.707 --> 10:41.541
DON'T GET A BACKLOG OF

10:41.541 --> 10:42.642
DELINQUENT ACCOUNTS THAT MAY

10:42.642 --> 10:44.010
ULTIMATELY GET SO OLD AND PEOPLE

10:44.010 --> 10:45.011
MOVE AWAY THAT WE'LL NEVER

10:45.011 --> 10:47.313
COLLECT IT.

10:47.313 --> 10:49.349
SO IT'S-- I THINK IT'S A

10:49.349 --> 10:50.950
WIN/WIN.

10:50.950 --> 10:52.051
>> I THINK PRIVATE PROBATION HAS

10:52.051 --> 10:53.653
A ROLE.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.555
>> Reporter: REPUBLICAN STATE

10:55.555 --> 10:57.156
SENATOR CAM WARD IS THE CHAIRMAN

10:57.156 --> 10:59.759
OF THE JUDICIARY COMMITTEE AND

10:59.759 --> 11:01.694
HAS BEEN FOLLOWING THE GROWING

11:01.694 --> 11:02.495
TREND OF PRIVATE PROBATION.

11:02.495 --> 11:03.663
NOT ONLY DOES WARD SUPPORT THE

11:03.663 --> 11:04.764
USE OF SUCH COMPANIES, HE

11:04.764 --> 11:05.632
BELIEVES THE INDUSTRY WILL

11:05.632 --> 11:07.066
CONTINUE TO GROW.

11:07.066 --> 11:08.167
>> NOW, I WILL TELL YOU THIS, I

11:08.167 --> 11:10.203
THINK THE TREND TO PRIVATIZATION

11:10.203 --> 11:11.538
IN THE AREA OF COLLECTIONS, I

11:11.538 --> 11:12.906
9THINK THAT WILL CONTINUE ALL

11:12.906 --> 11:14.407
ACROSS THE COUNTRY UNTIL YOU SEE

11:14.407 --> 11:15.441
A CONCENTRATED EFFORT TO PUT

11:15.441 --> 11:16.543
MORE MONEY INTO THE COLLECTION

11:16.543 --> 11:17.777
SERVICES THAT THE STATE RUNS.

11:17.777 --> 11:18.711
>> Reporter: BUT THESE PRIVATE

11:18.711 --> 11:19.646
DEBT COLLECTORS ARE BY

11:19.646 --> 11:20.747
DEFINITION IN BUSINESS TO MAKE

11:20.747 --> 11:21.681
MONEY.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.016
AND EVEN THOUGH THEY DON'T

11:23.016 --> 11:24.284
CHARGE THE CITY ANYTHING, THEY

11:24.284 --> 11:25.351
CHARGE OFFENDERS, LIKE TIMOTHY

11:25.351 --> 11:26.419
FUGATT, $45 A MONTH PLUS A $10

11:26.419 --> 11:27.353
START-UP FEE, UNTIL A DEBT IS

11:27.353 --> 11:29.088
FULLY PAID OFF.

11:29.088 --> 11:30.490
THIS ON TOP OF THE $500 IN COURT

11:30.490 --> 11:37.397
COSTS THAT FUGATT ALREADY OWED.

11:37.397 --> 11:38.364
CAN YOU TELL ME IF YOU WERE

11:38.364 --> 11:39.065
MAKING AN EFFORT TO PAY THESE

11:39.065 --> 11:40.033
OFF?

11:40.033 --> 11:40.967
>> WE WERE.

11:40.967 --> 11:41.734
YES, SIR.

11:41.734 --> 11:42.702
EVEN THOUGH, YOU KNOW, I WAS

11:42.702 --> 11:43.903
MAKING THE EFFORT, I WASN'T

11:43.903 --> 11:44.771
GETTING VERY FAR WITH IT.

11:44.771 --> 11:45.538
IT WAS-- IT WAS TILL ALL THESE

11:45.538 --> 11:46.372
FEES ADDING UP.

11:46.372 --> 11:49.208
SO I WASN'T GAINING MUCH GROUND.

11:49.208 --> 11:51.110
>> Reporter: STILL, FOUR MONTHS

11:51.110 --> 11:52.579
AFTER THEIR INITIAL COURT DATE,

11:52.579 --> 11:54.280
DOCUMENTS SHOW THAT THE FUGATTS'

11:54.280 --> 11:56.115
SCRAPED TOGETHER ENOUGH TO PAY

11:56.115 --> 11:57.383
OFF ALMOST $300 OF THE $500 THEY

11:57.383 --> 12:00.987
OWED IN COURT COSTS.

12:00.987 --> 12:02.455
♪

12:02.455 --> 12:04.524
BUT THEN THINGS WENT FROM BAD TO

12:04.524 --> 12:05.725
WORSE.

12:05.725 --> 12:08.361
IN JUNE OF 2011, THEIR SON,

12:08.361 --> 12:09.862
COLE, DIED.

12:09.862 --> 12:11.898
A MONTH LATER THEIR HOUSE THAT

12:11.898 --> 12:13.499
HAD BEEN IN THE FAMILY FOR

12:13.499 --> 12:14.901
GENERATIONS WAS FORECLOSED UPON.

12:14.901 --> 12:16.469
AT THIS POINT THE FUGATTS SAY

12:16.469 --> 12:17.670
THEY WERE CONSUMED WITH GRIEF

12:17.670 --> 12:18.938
AND WERE MISSING THEIR

12:18.938 --> 12:20.139
APPOINTMENTS WITH J.C.S.

12:20.139 --> 12:21.107
TIMOTHY SAYS HE EXPLAINED THE

12:21.107 --> 12:22.175
DIFFICULT CIRCUMSTANCES HIS

12:22.175 --> 12:23.309
FAMILY WAS UNDER, BUT HE SAYS

12:23.309 --> 12:24.110
THE J.C.S. PROBATION OFFICER

12:24.110 --> 12:30.483
WOULDN'T WORK WITH HIM AT ALL.

12:30.483 --> 12:31.484
>> IT WAS ALL AT ONE TIME, JUST

12:31.484 --> 12:32.385
HIT US ALL AT ONCE.

12:32.385 --> 12:33.720
AND I EXPLAINED IT ALL TO THEM.

12:33.720 --> 12:34.587
BUT WE-- YOU KNOW, IT WAS EITHER

12:34.587 --> 12:35.688
PAY OR GO TO JAIL.

12:35.688 --> 12:36.923
>> BEING THREATENED WITH A JAIL

12:36.923 --> 12:37.824
SENTENCE, DID THAT HELP YOU TO

12:37.824 --> 12:39.592
COME UP WITH THE MONEY?

12:39.592 --> 12:41.194
>> IT HELPED TO TRY A LITTLE

12:41.194 --> 12:42.528
HARDER, BUT, YOU KNOW, STILL.

12:42.528 --> 12:43.663
I MEAN, AS THE OLD SAYING GOES,

12:43.663 --> 12:44.731
YOU KNOW, YOU CAN'T SQUEEZE

12:44.731 --> 12:46.699
BLOOD FROM A TURNIP.

12:46.699 --> 12:48.234
>> Reporter: OVER THE NEXT EIGHT

12:48.234 --> 12:50.136
MONTHS WITH J.C.S. MONTHLY FEES

12:50.136 --> 12:51.571
ADDING UP, THE COUPLE MISSED AT

12:51.571 --> 12:52.972
LEAST ONE COURT DATE EACH AND

12:52.972 --> 12:54.841
WERE FINED ADDITIONAL FEES FOR

12:54.841 --> 12:58.511
FAILURE TO APPEAR.

12:58.511 --> 12:59.379
THEN A WARRANT FOR THEIR ARREST

12:59.379 --> 13:00.713
WAS ISSUED.

13:00.713 --> 13:02.048
BY THE TIME OF THEIR ARREST IN

13:02.048 --> 13:04.183
FEBRUARY OF 2012, THE FUGATTS

13:04.183 --> 13:05.385
HAD RACKED UP $2,500 IN

13:05.385 --> 13:07.120
ADDITIONAL COURT FINES.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.421
REMEMBER ALL THIS BEGAN WITH

13:08.421 --> 13:10.023
THREE TRAFFIC VIOLATIONS FOR

13:10.023 --> 13:11.290
WHICH THEY WERE FOUND NOT

13:11.290 --> 13:16.596
GUILTY.

13:16.596 --> 13:17.664
>> Reporter: IF YOU WOULD'VE

13:17.664 --> 13:18.631
COME UP WITH THE MONEY THAT YOU

13:18.631 --> 13:19.599
OWED JUDICIAL CORRECTION

13:19.599 --> 13:20.633
SERVICES AND YOU WOULD'VE SHOWN

13:20.633 --> 13:21.634
UP FOR ALL OF YOUR APPOINTMENTS

13:21.634 --> 13:22.735
WITH THEM AND TO THE COURTS,

13:22.735 --> 13:23.770
NONE OF THIS WOULD HAVE EVER

13:23.770 --> 13:26.239
HAPPENED?

13:26.239 --> 13:29.375
>> YOU'RE RIGHT.

13:29.375 --> 13:30.610
IT WOULDN'T HAVE HAPPENED, BUT,

13:30.610 --> 13:34.414
YOU KNOW, THE SITUATION I WAS

13:34.414 --> 13:35.281
IN, I WAS DOING WHAT I COULD DO,

13:35.281 --> 13:38.051
YOU KNOW?

13:38.051 --> 13:39.252
I HAD A DYING CHILD, NO STEADY

13:39.252 --> 13:40.119
JOB AT THAT POINT BECAUSE WE

13:40.119 --> 13:44.157
WERE BACK AND FORTH TO THE

13:44.157 --> 13:45.124
HOSPITAL, I WAS DOING WHAT I

13:45.124 --> 13:46.359
COULD DO.

13:46.359 --> 13:47.460
>> Reporter: DAVID DINELLI OF

13:47.460 --> 13:48.561
THE SOUTHERN POVERTY LAW CENTER

13:48.561 --> 13:49.562
SAYS THAT PEOPLE LIKE THE

13:49.562 --> 13:50.630
FUGATTS END UP PAYING J.C.S. OFF

13:50.630 --> 13:51.698
FOR YEARS BECAUSE OF ALL THE

13:51.698 --> 13:52.565
ADDITIONAL FEES AND ADDED FINES

13:52.565 --> 13:53.566
THAT THEY OFTEN ACCRUE.

13:53.566 --> 13:54.701
>> THEY'RE IN A SYSTEM IN WHICH

13:54.701 --> 13:55.968
ALL THEY ARE DOING IS PAYING

13:55.968 --> 13:57.170
J.C.S., JUDICIAL COLLECTION

13:57.170 --> 13:57.937
SERVICES ON A MONTHLY BASIS FOR

13:57.937 --> 13:59.005
THE PRIVILEGE OF STAYING OUT OF

13:59.005 --> 14:01.374
JAIL.

14:01.374 --> 14:02.642
>> Reporter: WE ASKED LEGAL

14:02.642 --> 14:04.177
SCHOLAR AND COLUMBIA LAW

14:04.177 --> 14:05.445
PROFESSOR GILLIAN METZGER TO

14:05.445 --> 14:07.647
TAKE A LOOK AT THE LAWSUIT AND

14:07.647 --> 14:08.648
TO EVALUATE THE

14:08.648 --> 14:09.682
CONSTITUTIONALITY OF PRIVATE

14:09.682 --> 14:10.650
COMPANIES, LIKE JUDICIAL

14:10.650 --> 14:11.684
CORRECTION SERVICES, COLLECTING

14:11.684 --> 14:12.652
FINES FOR CITIES LIKE

14:12.652 --> 14:13.252
CHILDERSBURG.

14:13.252 --> 14:14.220
SHE HAS NO INVOLVEMENT IN THE

14:14.220 --> 14:15.655
CASE.

14:15.655 --> 14:18.091
>> PART OF WHAT DUE PROCESS

14:18.091 --> 14:18.858
REQUIRES IS THAT YOU HAVE AN

14:18.858 --> 14:20.326
IMPARTIAL DECISION MAKER.

14:20.326 --> 14:21.227
AND IF THE COMPANY THAT IS

14:21.227 --> 14:22.195
IMPOSING THE FEES AND CONTINUING

14:22.195 --> 14:23.296
YOUR SUPERVISION HAS A FINANCIAL

14:23.296 --> 14:24.397
INTEREST IN YOUR STAYING UNDER

14:24.397 --> 14:27.734
SUPERVISION, THEN THAT REALLY

14:27.734 --> 14:29.135
CALLS THEIR IMPARTIALITY INTO

14:29.135 --> 14:30.269
QUESTION.

14:30.269 --> 14:31.104
AND THEY HAVE A FINANCIAL

14:31.104 --> 14:32.872
MOTIVE.

14:32.872 --> 14:33.940
>> Reporter: METZGER ALSO SAYS

14:33.940 --> 14:35.108
THE COURT IS OBLIGATED TO

14:35.108 --> 14:36.142
PROVIDE ALTERNATIVE OPTIONS FOR

14:36.142 --> 14:37.710
AN INDIVIDUAL TO PAY OFF A DEBT

14:37.710 --> 14:38.678
TO SOCIETY, SUCH AS COMMUNITY

14:38.678 --> 14:39.412
SERVICE, IF HE OR SHE IS

14:39.412 --> 14:40.980
INDIGENT.

14:40.980 --> 14:41.814
>> IF YOU'RE NOT PAYING BECAUSE

14:41.814 --> 14:42.815
YOU'RE JUST TOO POOR TO PAY,

14:42.815 --> 14:43.750
THEN THE COURT CAN'T

14:43.750 --> 14:44.851
AUTOMATICALLY IMPRISON YOU.

14:44.851 --> 14:45.985
THEY HAVE TO DO AN INVESTIGATION

14:45.985 --> 14:48.955
ABOUT ALTERNATIVE ARRANGEMENTS

14:48.955 --> 14:50.223
IN ORDER TO ALLOW YOU TO WORK

14:50.223 --> 14:50.990
OFF THE FINE IN SOME OTHER WAY.

14:50.990 --> 14:53.192
>> Reporter: WE REACHED OUT TO

14:53.192 --> 14:54.694
J.C.S. MULTIPLE TIMES FOR AN

14:54.694 --> 14:56.395
INTERVIEW, BUT WE NEVER RECEIVED

14:56.395 --> 14:57.497
A REPLY.

14:57.497 --> 15:03.002
BUT ON ITS WEBSITE J.C.S. SAYS

15:03.002 --> 15:04.771
THE LAWSUIT IS BASELESS.

15:04.771 --> 15:07.240
WE ALSO TRIED UNSUCCESSFULLY

15:07.240 --> 15:11.911
SEVERAL TIMES TO ASK THE MAYOR

15:11.911 --> 15:13.279
OF CHILDERSBURG, "B.J." MEEKS,

15:13.279 --> 15:14.280
IF HE WAS SATISFIED WITH THE

15:14.280 --> 15:15.214
SERVICES J.C.S. HAS BEEN

15:15.214 --> 15:15.915
PROVIDING THE CITY, BUT CITY

15:15.915 --> 15:16.916
HALL NEVER RESPONDED TO OUR

15:16.916 --> 15:17.717
REQUEST.

15:17.717 --> 15:18.785
SO WE WENT TO A CITY COUNCIL

15:18.785 --> 15:22.455
MEETING TO ASK.

15:22.455 --> 15:23.556
AFTER SPEAKING TO SOME OF THE

15:23.556 --> 15:24.457
RESIDENTS HERE, THEY FEEL LIKE

15:24.457 --> 15:25.358
THEY'VE BEEN THREATENED WITH A

15:25.358 --> 15:26.192
JAIL SENTENCE IF THEY DON'T PAY

15:26.192 --> 15:27.126
THEIR FINES AND I WONDER IF YOU

15:27.126 --> 15:28.161
HAD A COMMENT.

15:28.161 --> 15:28.995
>> WELL, THEN THAT'S UP TO THE

15:28.995 --> 15:29.695
COURT SYSTEM.

15:29.695 --> 15:35.034
IS, YOU KNOW...

15:35.034 --> 15:36.102
>> Reporter: I MEAN, IS IT NOT

15:36.102 --> 15:37.336
UNCONSTITUTIONAL TO JAIL

15:37.336 --> 15:38.704
SOMEBODY WHO CANNOT PAY THEIR

15:38.704 --> 15:41.741
FEE?

15:41.741 --> 15:43.276
>> I DON'T KNOW.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.544
AGAIN, IF THE COURT SYSTEM IS

15:44.544 --> 15:45.678
SATISFIED WITH IT UNDER STATE

15:45.678 --> 15:46.813
SUPREME COURT JURISDICTION, I

15:46.813 --> 15:49.782
KNOW THAT WE CONTRACT, WE ARE

15:49.782 --> 15:50.917
ONE OF THE MANY, MANY CITIES IN

15:50.917 --> 15:52.018
ALABAMA THAT USES CONTRACT

15:52.018 --> 15:52.919
SERVICE, AND THE REASON BEING

15:52.919 --> 15:54.053
BECAUSE OF NOT HAVING ENOUGH

15:54.053 --> 15:55.688
PERSONNEL, WE HAVE.

15:55.688 --> 15:56.489
>> Reporter: EVEN STATE SENATOR

15:56.489 --> 15:57.323
CAM WARD, WHO SUPPORTS THE

15:57.323 --> 15:58.291
PRIVATE PROBATION INDUSTRY, HAS

15:58.291 --> 15:59.125
CONCERNS.

15:59.125 --> 15:59.992
>> WHAT'S CURRENTLY IN EXISTENCE

15:59.992 --> 16:00.893
IS ALMOST LIKE THE WILD WEST.

16:00.893 --> 16:03.596
THERE IS NO REGULATION.

16:03.596 --> 16:07.767
IF YOU'RE GONNA CREATE A SYSTEM

16:07.767 --> 16:10.203
THAT IS A "DEBTORS PRISON," ALL

16:10.203 --> 16:11.904
YOU'RE DOING IS INVITING

16:11.904 --> 16:13.039
YOURSELF TO A FEDERAL LAWSUIT,

16:13.039 --> 16:17.210
IS WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

16:17.210 --> 16:18.277
>> Reporter: AS FOR THE FUGATTS,

16:18.277 --> 16:19.312
AFTER BEING CHARGED AN INITIAL

16:19.312 --> 16:20.246
COURT COST OF ABOUT $500 FOR

16:20.246 --> 16:21.280
TRAFFIC VIOLATIONS OF WHICH THEY

16:21.280 --> 16:22.181
WERE FOUND NOT GUILTY.

16:22.181 --> 16:23.049
COURT DOCUMENTS PROVIDED BY THE

16:23.049 --> 16:24.083
FUGATTS' LAWYERS SHOW THAT

16:24.083 --> 16:25.351
THEY'VE PAID ALMOST $1,300 TO

16:25.351 --> 16:26.285
THE CHILDERSBURG COURT.

16:26.285 --> 16:27.386
IT'S A NUMBER THAT DOESN'T EVEN

16:27.386 --> 16:28.254
INCLUDE ALL THE ADDITIONAL

16:28.254 --> 16:29.155
MONTHLY FEES THEY PAID TO

16:29.155 --> 16:31.724
JUDICIAL CORRECTION SERVICES.

16:31.724 --> 16:32.925
A FIGURE THE CITY OF

16:32.925 --> 16:34.260
CHILDERSBURG DECLINED TO PROVIDE

16:34.260 --> 16:39.265
US DUE TO PENDING LITIGATION.

16:39.265 --> 16:40.967
>> Reporter: TIMOTHY FUGATT SAYS

16:40.967 --> 16:42.168
THAT HIS FAMILY STILL OWES MORE

16:42.168 --> 16:43.603
MONEY TO JUDICIAL CORRECTIONS

16:43.603 --> 16:44.370
SERVICES.

16:44.370 --> 16:45.304
HOW MUCH?

16:45.304 --> 16:46.405
HE'S NOT SURE.

16:46.405 --> 16:48.374
HE SAYS J.C.S. STOPPED

16:48.374 --> 16:50.243
CONTACTING HIM AFTER THE LAWSUIT

16:50.243 --> 16:53.179
WAS FILED.

16:53.179 --> 16:54.747
WHILE THE FUGATT'S CASE IS STILL

16:54.747 --> 16:55.982
PENDING, SINCE OUR STORY AIRED

16:55.982 --> 16:57.617
LAST SPRING THE CHILDERSBURG

16:57.617 --> 17:02.154
MUNICIPAL COURT RECENTLY ISSUED

17:02.154 --> 17:03.189
A STANDING ORDER STATING THAT

17:03.189 --> 17:04.156
"IN NO CASE SHALL AN INDIGENT

17:04.156 --> 17:05.157
DEFENDANT BE INCARCERATED BASED

17:05.157 --> 17:06.559
SOLELY ON HIS OR HER INABILITY

17:06.559 --> 17:09.362
TO PAY FINES."

17:09.362 --> 17:11.497
FUGATT'S ATTORNEY ALSO TOLD

17:11.497 --> 17:13.366
NEWSHOUR THAT HUNDREDS OF

17:13.366 --> 17:14.634
CHILDERSBURG RESIDENTS NO LONGER

17:14.634 --> 17:16.168
HAVE WARRANTS OUT FOR THEIR

17:16.168 --> 17:17.837
